We work diligently to provide the best possible products to our customers. All of our items are handmade, from the product itself to the labeling on the bottles, by our two-person team. We are grateful for your support and take pride in our work. We are committed to only offering products that can rival the best in the industry and that is why there may be some waiting involved. Our new solution is not only silky smooth but will also ensure that your stencil lasts throughout your entire tattooing process. Additionally, it has a delightful fragrance, which is something we take great care in creating for all of our products. Our goal is to challenge the status quo and uplift artists within our community. In the near future, we plan to host live sessions with our artists and release merchandise designed by the very artists who inspire us. We value our relationship with each of our customers and consider them to be a part of our family. We are always open to feedback and suggestions because we recognize that they are essential to our growth. Finally, we want to emphasize that artists are the cornerstone of our company, and that will never change.

Caroline and I decided to do an interview with a good friend of ours and one of our sponsored artists recently. (You can see that on the @crybabytattooproducts instagram. )  After that I thought about how many people I really enjoy yet know very little about.  In this industry we usually catch each other at shows but hardly get to talk as we are all working.  I’m hoping to get stories from other tattooers to share with the world.  This is our small in home studio and I am so excited to get to work.  Still finding the right software that can do the job and it’s a bit of a learning curve if I’m being honest.  Once I feel comfortable with that I’d love to have more people on the  @crybaby_squadcast ! This has been such a fun way to get to know people and share the industry with the public. I can’t wait to hear all the fun stories from everyone.  And yes, the booth will eventually be all pink and blue but we have to start somewhere so my 70s decor is what I have to work with for now 😂 much love fam! (Also I know some of you have emailed me about getting on the podcast and I will be in touch! And if you want to email me , feel free and I’ll get ya on the list! Crybabytattooaftercare@gmail.com) I can’t wait to hear all the crazy tattooer stories as well as maybe bringing on some clients!

Used my @inkjecta tattoo machine today for the first time.  I bought the inkjecta flite x1 wireless machine.  I’ve ordered a few others and wasn’t really happy.Not saying they weren’t good machines , just weren’t for my hand and how I tattoo. As a machine builder myself, I have some pretty high standards and this machine met them all .  I think if I had to describe the machine , it’s a good in between machine of a coil and pen. Though a tad top heavy as far as the machine, there was no fighting in any part of the tattoo. Very happy with this product. Paired with @crybabytattooproducts  and I can’t go wrong! The stencil bond is amazing along with the tattoo glide.  Go check it out!

Thank you so much for having us out this weekend at the @trilogytattoo conference! This group of seminars was amazing.  We enjoyed @badcaseofpurpose showing us all about stacking and layering and how to add more to your tools using other styles to incorporate into your own.  We loved hearing from @theangelrose about how the speeds of your machines can create different effects when it comes to black and grey along with tons of helpful tips about advanced lighting. And @tattoosbylauramarie about how she draws inspiration from magic the gathering and DND.  Along with tips about flow and angles getting your piece aligned with the body.  It was an amazing seminar with amazing people.  We had a wonderful lunch and dinner and got to mingle with some other incredible artists! If they do this again in the future, you should go! Thanks for trusting @crybabytattooproducts to sponsor your event and letting us soak up the knowledge.

Crybaby has provided such a home for myself and others. I feel like tattooing is the black sheep in the art community. Now imagine being the black sheep inside that community.  I’ve had the respect of artists and lost it when they found out I was trans/pan or whatever other reason.  Then all the sudden I was erased and not thought of as a peer. I was ignored, not invited, laughed at , pushed to the side , etc .  I think many people in this industry can relate to me.  I’m not the only person with this story. You have to claw your way in. 
If you’re a minority that’s no news to you. 
Caroline and I built our shop up with the help from friends and contractors and we had no aftercare to match our pastel dream.  My casual attitude of ,”It can’t be that hard.” Happened and I decided to try my hand at creating our own.  That was also one of the hardest parts about this.  It took 1.5 years to get right. Many times I almost threw in the towel, but Caroline pushed me to keep going.  I’m so thankful for that.  Making salve was not easy 😂. But the good things never are.  Finally we got it. I posted a photo and sold my first salve in Australia and Europe. I noticed, we might not be alone here.  So we decided to turn this into a business. After all tattooing doesn’t have a retirement plan. I worked 3 years for free the longest days I’d worked in a long time on top of tattooing full time.  Missing time with my wife and friends.It’s finally coming together.  I had no idea what we had worked so hard for could be so much more. It was groups of the most amazing people coming forward to support and show love. We finally had a place to come together.  To find one another and to support each other.  You cannot put a price on that.  It opened me up to so many new styles of tattooing I’d never thought about.  It brought so many amazing friends into my life. Crybaby became the name bc that’s what everyone called us anyhow. It’s great to see my friends rise to the top with their own platforms.  We didn’t create it all. I’d like to think we had our place in it. That you cannot put a price on. I love all you Crybabies. There’s more to this, I’ll save that for a podcast but thank you all

Our hearts go out to our friends and 'ohana in Maui who have been deeply affected by the recent wildfires. On August 8, 2023, a devastating combination of drought conditions and hurricane weather resulted in widespread wildfires across Maui. Families were abruptly evacuated, often with only the clothes they were wearing. Information about injuries and casualties is still emerging. Regrettably, Lahaina town has been completely destroyed, and other areas on Maui have also suffered. Our thoughts and prayers remain with this remarkable community. 
  But we can do even better by donating. With every 8oz jar purchased we will donate $3 , with every 1oz ($1 donation) ,and with every 12 pack($4 donation )and with every 24 pack ($6 donation) and all of those donations will be directly sent from us to the foundation.  We are really asking anyone who can help to help.  We knew as a company we would do all we could to stand firm and help those in need bc it’s what is right and what we believe in. We won’t line our pockets while watching other families and people suffer. It’s times like these we pull together. (Donations starting now.  Ending at the end of Aug.  we will push out that deadline if more donations are needed) 

Please if you can donate on your own if you’re able to as well, donate to www.hawaiicommunityfoundation.org/maui-strong ! Even if it’s $5 this could really help someone in need. 

 Find the link in our bio! Share this post if you can. Thank you.

Our mission was clear from the start — to shine the spotlight on minorities and women in the industry, striving to level the playing field. The products we've meticulously crafted are a testament to our dedication. While pink might not be everyone's preference, it symbolizes our commitment to addressing the lack of representation for various groups. We deliberately chose our first proteam members to be women and minorities, standing firmly behind our principles.

We proudly endorse everything we create, say, and do. The support from incredible artists and individuals has been gratifying. One such remarkable person is @mikendazzoart , with whom we've collaborated. He designed the whole packaging and it came out beautifully! Mike's integrity aligns seamlessly with ours, making the journey into the dark side of Crybaby even more exciting. 

2% of all proceeds of this line will be donated to breast cancer research of Mikes choosing!!!! 

The collaboration has been enlightening, and the insights gained have been invaluable. Get ready for the launch of our new Goth Crybaby aka Gothbaby  line on Black Friday. The Ointment carries a delightful fruity loop scent and the Stencil Bond has a berry scent. Committed to skin health, all our ointments are 100% fragrance-free, using only natural oils to promote healing. We sincerely hope you enjoy our offerings.
